 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# LDDMM: how to estimate a deterministic atlas?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This is analog to a registration problem for multiple meshes.\n",
    "\n",
    "For registration between two meshes check [LDDMM: how to register a mesh to a template?](./lddmm_register_mesh_template.ipynb) and [LDDMM: how to visualize registration results?](./lddmm_register_mesh_template_viz.ipynb). "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "No CUDA runtime is found, using CUDA_HOME='/usr'\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pyvista as pv\n",
    "\n",
    "import polpo.lddmm as plddmm\n",
    "import polpo.preprocessing.dict as ppdict\n",
    "import polpo.utils as putils\n",
    "from polpo.plot.pyvista import RegisteredMeshesGifPlotter\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing import (\n",
    "    Map,\n",
    "    PartiallyInitializedStep,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.load.pregnancy import (\n",
    "    DenseMaternalMeshLoader,\n",
    ")\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mesh.io import PvReader, PvWriter\n",
    "from polpo.preprocessing.mesh.registration import PvAlign"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "VIZ = False\n",
    "STATIC_VIZ = True\n",
    "\n",
    "if STATIC_VIZ:\n",
    "    pv.set_jupyter_backend(\"static\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "OUTPUTS_DIR = Path(\"results\") / \"atlas_example\"\n",
    "ATLAS_DIR = OUTPUTS_DIR / \"atlas\"\n",
    "\n",
    "OUTPUTS_DIR.mkdir(exist_ok=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading meshes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "subject_id = \"01\"\n",
    "\n",
    "file_finder = DenseMaternalMeshLoader(\n",
    "    subject_id=subject_id,\n",
    "    subset=[1, 2, 3],\n",
    "    as_dict=False,\n",
    "    left=True,\n",
    "    struct=\"Hipp\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "pipe = file_finder + Map(PvReader())\n",
    "\n",
    "meshes = pipe()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if VIZ:\n",
    "    pl = pv.Plotter(border=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "    for mesh in meshes:\n",
    "        pl.add_mesh(mesh, show_edges=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    pl.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "prep_pipe = PartiallyInitializedStep(\n",
    "    Step=lambda **kwargs: Map(PvAlign(**kwargs)),\n",
    "    _target=lambda meshes: meshes[0],\n",
    "    max_iterations=500,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "meshes = prep_pipe(meshes)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "if VIZ:\n",
    "    pl = pv.Plotter(border=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "    for mesh in meshes:\n",
    "        pl.add_mesh(mesh, show_edges=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "    pl.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## LDDMM"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Save meshes in `vtk` format (as required by `deformetrica`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "meshes_writer = Map(PvWriter(dirname=OUTPUTS_DIR, ext=\"vtk\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset = meshes_writer([(f\"mesh_{index}\", mesh) for index, mesh in enumerate(meshes)])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Use LDDMM to estimate the atlas."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Logger has been set to: DEBUG\n",
      ">> No initial CP spacing given: using diffeo kernel width of 10.0\n",
      "OMP_NUM_THREADS was not found in environment variables. An automatic value will be set.\n",
      "OMP_NUM_THREADS will be set to 10\n",
      "context has already been set\n",
      ">> No specified state-file. By default, Deformetrica state will by saved in file: results/atlas_example/atlas/deformetrica-state.p.\n",
      ">> Using a Sobolev gradient for the template data with the ScipyLBFGS estimator memory length being larger than 1. Beware: that can be tricky.\n",
      "{'max_iterations': 2000, 'freeze_template': False, 'freeze_control_points': False, 'freeze_momenta': False, 'use_sobolev_gradient': True, 'sobolev_kernel_width_ratio': 1, 'max_line_search_iterations': 50, 'initial_control_points': None, 'initial_cp_spacing': None, 'initial_momenta': None, 'dense_mode': False, 'number_of_threads': 1, 'print_every_n_iters': 20, 'downsampling_factor': 1, 'dimension': 3, 'optimization_method_type': 'ScipyLBFGS', 'convergence_tolerance': 1e-10, 'initial_step_size': 0.1, 'gpu_mode': <GpuMode.KERNEL: 4>, 'state_file': 'results/atlas_example/atlas/deformetrica-state.p', 'load_state_file': False, 'memory_length': 10}\n",
      "instantiating kernel torch with kernel_width 10.0 and gpu_mode GpuMode.KERNEL. addr: 0x7bf0746c6f10\n",
      "instantiating kernel torch with kernel_width 2.0 and gpu_mode GpuMode.KERNEL. addr: 0x7bf0743201d0\n",
      ">> Set of 24 control points defined.\n",
      ">> Momenta initialized to zero, for 3 subjects.\n",
      "dtype=float32\n",
      ">> Started estimator: ScipyOptimize\n",
      "\n",
      ">> Scipy optimization method: L-BFGS-B\n",
      "\n",
      "------------------------------------- Iteration: 1 -------------------------------------\n",
      ">> Gradient at Termination: 1209275.3414996846\n",
      ">> CONVERGENCE: REL_REDUCTION_OF_F_<=_FACTR*EPSMCH\n",
      ">> Estimation took: 09 seconds\n",
      "Deformetrica.__del__()\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "kernel_width = 10.0  # NB: influences the number of cp\n",
    "registration_kwargs = dict(\n",
    "    kernel_width=kernel_width,\n",
    "    regularisation=1,\n",
    "    max_iter=2000,\n",
    "    freeze_control_points=False,\n",
    "    metric=\"varifold\",\n",
    "    attachment_kernel_width=2.0,\n",
    "    tol=1e-10,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "plddmm.estimate_deterministic_atlas(\n",
    "    source=dataset[0],  # TODO: why do we need a source?\n",
    "    targets=dataset,\n",
    "    output_dir=ATLAS_DIR,\n",
    "    initial_step_size=1e-1,\n",
    "    **registration_kwargs,\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Visualize the results."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cp, momenta = plddmm.io.load_cp_and_momenta(ATLAS_DIR)\n",
    "template = plddmm.io.load_template(ATLAS_DIR, as_pv=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "data": {

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pl = pv.Plotter()\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.add_mesh(template, show_edges=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.add_mesh(pv.PolyData(cp))\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Visualize the reconstruction errors."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "rec_meshes = plddmm.io.load_deterministic_atlas_reconstructions(ATLAS_DIR, as_pv=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/jpeg": "",
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot_shape = putils.plot_shape_from_n_plots(len(meshes), n_axis=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "pl = pv.Plotter(shape=plot_shape, border=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "# TODO: make this better after cleaning ids\n",
    "for index, (mesh, rec_mesh) in enumerate(zip(meshes, rec_meshes.values())):\n",
    "    pl.subplot(*putils.plot_index_to_shape(index, plot_shape[1]))\n",
    "\n",
    "    # NB: assumes meshes are registered\n",
    "    euc_res = np.linalg.norm(mesh.points - rec_mesh.points, axis=-1)\n",
    "    pl.add_mesh(rec_mesh, scalars=euc_res)\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Visualize the flow from the template to each of the meshes."

  },
  {

    "gif_dir = OUTPUTS_DIR / \"_images\"\n",
    "gif_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "gif_name = gif_dir / \"flow.gif\"\n",
    "\n",
    "pl = RegisteredMeshesGifPlotter(\n",
    "    shape=putils.plot_shape_from_n_plots(len(meshes), n_axis=2),\n",

    "    fps=10,\n",
    "    border=False,\n",
    "    off_screen=True,\n",
    "    notebook=False,\n",
    "    subtitle=True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.add_meshes(ppdict.DictListSwapper()(flows))\n",
    "pl.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "pl.show()"
